    {
        "url": "/quotes/harvey_pekar_604218",
        "quote": "I always wanted praise, and I always wanted attention; I won't lie to you. I was a jazz critic, and that wasn't good enough for me. I wanted people to write about me, not me about them. So I thought, 'What could I do? I can't sing, I can't dance, I can't act or anything like that. OK, I can write.'",
        "author": {
            "name": "Harvey Pekar",
            "url": "/quotes/harvey_pekar_604218"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Thought",
